
[1]incorrigible

   INCOR'RIGIBLE, a. [L. corrigo; con and rego.]

   1. That cannot be corrected or amended; bad beyond correction; as
   incorrigible error.

   2. Too depraved to be corrected or reformed; as an incorrigible sinner;
   an incorrigible drunkard.
